<span id="freeTextContainer16396254725434400568">Evidently even modern kids can enjoy these classic stories of the brilliant young detective. I checked this one out of the library for my reluctant-reader eight year old grandson and he dove right in. He&apos;s read it twice and asked me to get more next time I&apos;m there. <br/><br/>Part of the attraction is that each story is only a couple of pages long. Then the reader is asked to identify what clues Encyclopedia used to solve the case, and given the page they can turn to and see if they got it right. This inte</span>
  <span id="freeText16396254725434400568" style="display:none">Evidently even modern kids can enjoy these classic stories of the brilliant young detective. I checked this one out of the library for my reluctant-reader eight year old grandson and he dove right in. He's read it twice and asked me to get more next time I'm there. <br /><br />Part of the attraction is that each story is only a couple of pages long. Then the reader is asked to identify what clues Encyclopedia used to solve the case, and given the page they can turn to and see if they got it right. This interaction keeps the reader going happily through the book. I remember devouring these when I was little. I'm glad they're still around for my grandkids. :)</span>
